From cd3143c71173e67226dc8102b49a3b304162dcdf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chris Liddell <chris.liddell@artifex.com>
Date: Thu, 22 Jun 2023 13:56:07 +0100
Subject: Bug 706793: Allow reusing underlying font objects

Store a custom entry in a FontDescriptor object which is the font object we're
created. If the FontDescriptor is shared between multiple font objects we can
then reuse the font, and save recreating it multiple times.
---
 pdf/pdf_font.c   | 165 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------------------------
 pdf/pdf_font1.c  |   2 -
 pdf/pdf_font1C.c |   2 -
 pdf/pdf_fontTT.c |   2 -
 4 files changed, 93 insertions(+), 78 deletions(-)

